Getting started

Source: vignettes/phenOncoX.Rmd
phenOncoX.Rmd



Installation 


if (!("remotes" %in% installed.packages()) {
  install.packages("remotes")
}
remotes::install_github('sigven/phenOncoX')



Get OncoTree terms

This shows how to retrieve cancer phenotype terms in, as defined in OncoTree (max tree depth = 2)


## load the data
download_dir <- tempdir()

oncotree <- phenOncoX::get_tree(
  cache_dir = download_dir, max_tree_depth = 2)
#> INFO  [2022-12-13 09:58:34] Downloading remote dataset from Google Drive to cache_dir
#> INFO  [2022-12-13 09:58:35] Reading from cache_dir = '/tmp/RtmpGkcU9K', argument force_download = FALSE
#> INFO  [2022-12-13 09:58:35] Object 'oncotree_core' sucessfully loaded
#> INFO  [2022-12-13 09:58:35] md5 checksum is valid: 8883ead04178ac6fb131d0e6e6424ac1
#> INFO  [2022-12-13 09:58:35] Retrieved 797 records
#> INFO  [2022-12-13 09:58:35] Limiting OncoTree terms to those with a maximum tree depth of = '2'

## Number of records
nrow(oncotree$records)
#> [1] 253

## Show metadata for underlying resources
oncotree$metadata
#>     source                                       annotation_data
#> 1 OncoTree A cancer classification system for precision oncology
#>                                url
#> 1 http://oncotree.mskcc.org/#/home
#>                                                citation    version abbreviation
#> 1 Kundra et al., JCO Clin Cancer Inform, 2021; 33625877 2021_11_02     oncotree



Get all (OncoTree-expanded) cancer phenotype terms 


## get all cancer phenotype terms

oncoterms <- phenOncoX::get_terms(
  cache_dir = download_dir)
#> INFO  [2022-12-13 09:58:35] Downloading remote dataset from Google Drive to cache_dir
#> INFO  [2022-12-13 09:58:38] Reading from cache_dir = '/tmp/RtmpGkcU9K', argument force_download = FALSE
#> INFO  [2022-12-13 09:58:38] Object 'oncotree_expanded' sucessfully loaded
#> INFO  [2022-12-13 09:58:38] md5 checksum is valid: b4726214edf9aa570971f94ca5c2e9e9
#> INFO  [2022-12-13 09:58:38] Retrieved 23896 records

## Number of records
nrow(oncoterms$records)
#> [1] 23896



Get all (OncoTree-expanded) cancer phenotype terms relevant for prostate cancer 


## get all oncoterms for prostate cancer
oncoterms_prostate <- phenOncoX::get_terms(
  cache_dir = download_dir, 
  site = "Prostate")

## Make as datatable
prostate_terms_table <- DT::datatable(
  dplyr::select(
    oncoterms_prostate$records, 
    primary_site, cui, cui_name,
    dplyr::everything()),
  escape = FALSE,
  extensions = c("Buttons", "Responsive"), 
  width = "100%",
  options = list(
    buttons = c("csv", "excel"), 
    dom = "Bfrtip"))
